The paper deals with the exploration and analysis of a large knowledge base, Freebase, which is a structured dataset containing billions of RDF triples. This makes it relevant to the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of Freebase data in information retrieval (IR) and knowledge-based question answering (KBQA), which are sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The methodology used in the paper involves the use of open-source Unix-like tools, which is relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the technique used, which is relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY).
